The {{SQUAD_NAME}} squad delivers {{PROJECT_NAME}} features through an EXECUTION pipeline owned by {{LEAD_SEAT_NAME}}. Discovery — brainstorm, research, codebase exploration, product/architecture design — happens UPSTREAM in native Claude Code and arrives as a ready backlog doc; the squad starts at execution, never at an ambiguous request.

ROUTING: assign feature and bugfix issues to {{LEAD_SEAT_NAME}}, who runs the pipeline (readiness check → decompose into turnkey sub-issues → Builder implements → deterministic risk-routed review on top of the {{CI_BASELINE_REVIEWER}} CI baseline → {{QA_SEAT_NAME}} e2e where behavior changed → final PR to the human). Do NOT dispatch a substantive feature directly to a member — only a trivial, unambiguous fix goes straight to {{BUILDER_SEAT_NAME}}. The human workspace owner is the product owner and the only one who merges to {{TARGET_BRANCH}}.

HUMAN CONTROL: the human's observability/abort levers over a running pipeline are `multica issue runs {id}` (status) and `multica issue cancel-task {task-id}` (surgical interrupt of one stuck task); {{LEAD_SEAT_NAME}} surfaces these inline in its orchestration comment. <!-- STANDARD+ only: the watchdog-arm lever below requires a Monitor watchdog seat + autopilot; omit at MIN (Lead-reconciler-only) -->After filing an issue, the human may also ARM the stall watchdog immediately without waiting for the Lead's Phase-1 arm: `multica autopilot update {{WATCHDOG_AUTOPILOT_UUID}} --status active` (idempotent — the Lead re-asserts it every wake and {{MONITOR_SEAT_NAME}} pauses it when the board idles), which closes the residual where a Lead that never ran at intake never armed the watchdog. Each squad agent's own instructions carry the shared constitution (untrusted-data, guardrails, secrets, mention directory, verdict grammar) and its role card; this squad note governs only how work is routed to the leader.
